</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1399,1327,1532]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
This species was originally described in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moczar 1971)" baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[659,993,1327,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Heterocoelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[659,811,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Heterocoelia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar L." box="[826,984,1327,1353]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="295 - 332" refId="ref7629" refString="Moczar L. 1971. Mestinae of world, genera &quot; Mesitius spinola &quot;, Pilomesitius Moczar, Parvoculus Moczar, Pycnomesitius Moczar and Heterocoelia Dahlbom. III. (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 17: 295 - 332." type="journal article" year="1971">Móczár 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1210,1327,1353]" name="South Africa" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar L." box="[1225,1385,1327,1353]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="295 - 332" refId="ref7629" refString="Moczar L. 1971. Mestinae of world, genera &quot; Mesitius spinola &quot;, Pilomesitius Moczar, Parvoculus Moczar, Pycnomesitius Moczar and Heterocoelia Dahlbom. III. (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 17: 295 - 332." type="journal article" year="1971">Móczár 1971</bibRefCitation>
), and later recorded from the 
<collectingCountry box="[532,794,1362,1388]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O." box="[813,1130,1362,1389]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="375 - 404" refId="ref7132" refString="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O. 2011 Order Hymenoptera, family Bethylidae, subfamily Mesitiinae. In: Harten A. van (ed.) Arthropod Fauna of UAE. Vol. 4: 375 - 404. Dar Al Ummah Printing, Publishing, Distribution &amp; Advertising, Abu Dhabi." type="journal article" year="2011">Barbosa &amp; Azevedo 2011</bibRefCitation>
). It was transferred to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[189,332,1399,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Metrionotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,332,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metrionotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar L." box="[381,563,1398,1424]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="173 - 177" refId="ref7675" refString="Moczar L. 1974. On another species of the genus Metrionotus Moczar (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae: Mesitiinae). Acta Biologica, Szeged 20: 173 - 177." type="journal article" year="1974">Móczár (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. We examined the 
<typeStatus box="[793,896,1398,1424]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
male from 
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1100,1398,1424]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">UAE</collectingCountry>
identified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="375 - 404" refId="ref7132" refString="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O. 2011 Order Hymenoptera, family Bethylidae, subfamily Mesitiinae. In: Harten A. van (ed.) Arthropod Fauna of UAE. Vol. 4: 375 - 404. Dar Al Ummah Printing, Publishing, Distribution &amp; Advertising, Abu Dhabi." type="journal article" year="2011">Barbosa &amp; Azevedo (2011)</bibRefCitation>
and deposited at UFES, and the analyses, mainly of the hypopygium, reveal that their characteristics perfectly fit 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[505,664,1470,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[505,664,1470,1496]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[671,777,1470,1496]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Thus, we propose a new combination for this species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[253,396,1506,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Metrionotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[253,396,1506,1531]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metrionotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[434,593,1506,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[434,593,1506,1532]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[600,708,1506,1532]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
